<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1058,731,841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">D e s c r i p t i o n o f b r a c h y p t e r o u s m a l e: Measurements: Body length 5.8-5.9; body width 3.8-4.0. Head length 1.20-1.26; head width (across eyes) 1.45- 1.48. Pronotum length (at midline) 0.74-0.80; pronotum width 3.19-3.20. Rostrum length 2.03. Profemur length 1.49.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1059,857,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">
Colour: Body and appendages chiefly pale yellow. Dorsal colour pattern as in 
<figureCitation box="[964,1053,857,879]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[151,184,1390,1412]" captionTargetBox="[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp., habitus of brachypterous male (holotype); legs omitted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038840/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">Figure 1</figureCitation>
: Pronotum anteriorly with a wide, blurred, M-shaped mark, posteriorly with a narrow transverse blackish brown stripe. Forewing remnants dark brown, sides yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1059,857,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">Abdominal tergites chiefly medium brown, sides of tergites anteriorly dark brown, posteriorly yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1058,1011,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">
Structures: Head 0.84 times as long as broad; anterior part (in front of anterior eye margin) very short, 0.38 times eye length (
<figureCitation box="[491,549,1041,1063]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[151,184,1390,1412]" captionTargetBox="[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp., habitus of brachypterous male (holotype); legs omitted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038840/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Head dorsally with very few large and numerous small punctures, shiny. Sides of pronotum, forewings and tergites coriaceous, matt. Disc of pronotum and middle of mesoscutellum rugulous-punctate, shiny. Anterior and posterior margin of pronotum transversely rugulose. Pronotum strongly transverse, 4.15 times as broad as median length, without demarcated lateral areas; hind margin laterally almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[240,298,1187,1209]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[151,184,1390,1412]" captionTargetBox="[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp., habitus of brachypterous male (holotype); legs omitted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038840/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutellum 2.5 times as broad as long. Forewings clearly distant from each other, caudally almost reaching hind margin of tergite 2 (
<figureCitation box="[795,853,1217,1239]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[151,184,1390,1412]" captionTargetBox="[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp., habitus of brachypterous male (holotype); legs omitted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038840/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), with obtuse angle at embolar margin; forewing width about one third longer than length (1.81: 1.35). Connexival margins of abdominal segment 2 and 3 nearly rectangular, of segments 4–6 with small, acute tip, of segment 7 acutely protruded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1059,1342,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">
Rostrum of medium length, 1.36 times as long as profemur, slightly surpassing posterior margin of mesosternum. Legs relatively short and stout; femora slightly thickened and hardly surpassing body sides. Propleuron mesally with an acuminate process (
<figureCitation box="[979,1045,1401,1423]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[151,191,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[156,1059,371,939]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[154,1065,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038848/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Mesosternum with blunt median carina, steadily raised from anterior to posterior margin, its outline only slightly convex in lateral aspect (
<figureCitation box="[647,710,1459,1481]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[151,191,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[156,1059,371,939]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[154,1065,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038848/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Abdomen weakly asymmetrical. Tergite 5 roundly protruded in middle (
<figureCitation box="[544,602,1489,1511]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[151,184,1390,1412]" captionTargetBox="[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp., habitus of brachypterous male (holotype); legs omitted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038840/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Sternites medially without posteriad direct- ed processes, sternites 4–6 each with one pair of peg-like, standing setae near middle of hind margin (lacking on sternite 
<quantity box="[483,522,1547,1569]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140" unit="in" value="6.0">6 in</quantity>
<specimenCount box="[528,672,1547,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1140" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
).
</paragraph>
