<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1059,1463,1573]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1058,211,321]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1142" pageId="2" pageNumber="1141">
Genitalia of male: Genital capsule posteriorly slightly acuminate (
<figureCitation box="[828,892,1463,1485]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[151,191,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[156,1059,371,939]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[154,1065,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038848/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1141">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), apex narrowly rounded. Parandria (
<figureCitation box="[355,415,1493,1515]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[151,191,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[156,1059,371,939]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[154,1065,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038848/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1141">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) strongly developed, left one surpassing right one; left paramere wide, apex rounded and slightly curved mesally; right parandrium distally with a roundish swelling. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[367,431,1551,1573]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[151,191,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[156,1059,371,939]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[154,1065,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038848/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1141">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) consisting of a narrow, basally slightly widened sclerotised strap and wide membraneous dilatations on both sides. Right paramere (
<figureCitation box="[875,969,211,233]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[151,191,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[156,1059,371,939]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[154,1065,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038848/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Figs. 5, 6</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than left one, apex narrower; on lateral side with a subbasal strongly furrowed process; pilosity on ventral side extremely long. Left paramere (
<figureCitation box="[799,894,270,292]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[151,191,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[156,1059,371,939]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[154,1065,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038848/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Figs. 7, 8</figureCitation>
) broadly subtriangular, with a widely rounded apex; pilosity on ventral side short.
</paragraph>
